  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0bb2\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f 6 \u0b86\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Deputy National Security Adviser Level 6 Conference of National Security Council of India successfully concluded",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "India, Maldives, Mauritius and Sri Lanka successfully completed the 6th Deputy National Security Adviser Level Conference organized by National Security Council of India in Kochi on Thursday (07).",
        "India's Deputy National Security Adviser Shri Vikram Mishri, Maldives Foreign Secretary Ahmed Ladeep, Mauritius Prime Minister's Office Chief Attach\u00e9 for Security Affairs Joythishthir Thekka and Sri Lankan Defense Forces Chief General Shavendra Silva presided over their delegations.",
        "Commodore MH Nishantha Peiris, Director of Foreign Affairs, Director of Maritime Operations and Acting Secretary of the Sri Lanka Navy, represented the Colombo Secretariat of the Colombo Defense Group and participated in the conference.",
        "Meanwhile, the delegation from Bangladesh was led by the Chief Security Officer of the Armed Forces, Lt. Gen. Wager Ush Shaman, while the Chief of Defense Forces of Seychelles, Simon Archangel Dine represented Seychelles in this conference.",
        "Implementation of the Roadmap for Cooperation for the period 2022 - 2023 and the 5th National Security Adviser-level Conference of the Colombo Joint Security Group held in the Maldives on 9-10 March 2022 on maritime security and security, countering terrorism and radicalisation, combating trafficking and transnational organized crime, cyber security, critical infrastructure It is noteworthy that the participants in the conference discussed technical security, humanitarian aid and disaster relief."
      ],
